<h2>Vertical Tabbed Interface using Accordion Widget</h2>

<div id="vertical_tabs">
    <h3>What is Integration</h3>
    <div>An integration enables third-party services to call the Magento web APIs. The Magento APIs currently supports Accounting,
        Enterprise Resource Planning (ERP), Customer Relationship Management (CRM), Product Information Management (PIM), and
        marketing automation systems out of the box. </div>

    <h3>What is Redis</h3>
    <div>Redis is an optional backend cache solution to replace Zend_Cache_Backend_File, which is used in Magento 2 by default.</div>

    <h3>What is Varnish</h3>
    <div>Varnish Cache is an open source web application accelerator (also referred to as an HTTP accelerator or caching HTTP
        reverse proxy). Varnish stores (or caches) files or fragments of files in memory; this enables Varnish to reduce the response
        time and network bandwidth consumption on future, equivalent requests. Unlike web servers like Apache and nginx,
        Varnish was designed for use exclusively with the HTTP protocol.

        Magento 2 supports Varnish versions 3.0.5 or later or any Varnish 4.x version.
    </div>
</div>

